Rabiu Kwankwaso, the Presidential candidate of the New Nigeria Peoples Party, NNPP, has appealed to President Muhammadu Buhari to leave a legacy of a free election. Kwankwaso made this known in a tweet on Wednesday. According to him, he has learnt that free and fair elections require the contribution of different stakeholders, especially the President. ”My 30 years in elections have taught me that free and fair elections require the contributions of different stakeholders, especially the president, if the president wants a fair election, it will happen. “I want to appeal to the Nigerian president to leave a legacy of free elections, as a serial victim of electoral fraud, and as the first beneficiary of free and fair elections in Nigeria.” ”Thank you for listening, thank you.” – RMK’, the tweet said.’